        "title": "JAVA passing argument",
        "body": "<p>I know that JAVA is passing arguments by value (copy). Why does this code returns John ?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class User {\n    String name;\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        User u = new User();\n        u.name = \"Sebastian\";\n        System.out.println(u.name);\n        initialize(u);\n        System.out.println(u.name);\n    }\n    public static void initialize(User u){\n        u.name = \"John\";\n        System.out.println(u.name);\n        User u2 = new User();\n        u2.name=\"dsafsa\";\n        u = u2;\n        System.out.println(u.name);\n        u.name = \"Lilly\";\n        System.out.println(u.name);\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
